cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.NE, cs.CY, cs.CV

The paper discusses the use of physiological signals to analyze users' perceptual experience of multimedia, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of wearable physiological sensors and the analysis of cerebral physiological signals also suggest a connection to neuroscience and neural engineering (cs.NE). The paper also discusses current trends and challenges, which could potentially fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the analysis of physiological signals is used to improve computer vision systems.
